args: Thank you for visiting our store!\nNew customers are always welcome.
We were hoping that madam might be\nable to repair this lance. Yes, quite.
Well, let me take a look.
Pray give me your hand in marriage!
Okay, so that's one lance repair\nand one marriage proposal. Got it.
I'm baaaaack! Hey, so who was the fancy\nguy with Jeeves the butler back there?\nSome kind of rich weapon nut?
Soon, word that a wealthy noble had asked Rena\nto marry him spread throughout the castle.
The noble returned to the store day\nafter day seeking Rena's answer...
...Sweet Rena! Please do me the honor\nof becoming my wife!
My apologies, sir, but without me here,\nour smithy would have no one to run it.\nI am afraid my answer must be no.
...Darling Rena! Your constant rejections\nare like daggers through my broken heart!\nPlease change your mind! Pleeeeease!
What's that? You have a broken dagger?\nWell, we can fix that right up!

...Beloved Rena! I climbed the highest
mountain in the land and fought twenty
dragons to claim the rare jewel that rests
in this engagement ring! Please say yes!
Oooo, sorry. I really like these gloves,\nsee, and there's no way I can fit a ring\nover them. Such a shame. Toodles!
I'm startin' to think we're gonna have to\ntattoo Rena's rejection on that joker's\nface so he finally gets it.

Aw, I think it's kinda sweet. I mean,
he's not creepy or anything—he's
just in love. ...Plus, he's super rich,
which never huuuurts!
But Rena seems pretty convinced\nthis isn't the guy for her.
Yeah, maybe he's just not her type.\nOr...I dunno. Maybe there's somethin'\nelse goin' on here.

Why, Rena?! Why will you not marry me?!
With every rejection, my heart shrivels
more—soon it will be naught but a
blackened, empty husk!

Is there something you dislike about me?
It will be changed! ...Wait, is it my hair?
Do you not like my hair? Consider it gone!
...Jeeves, come shave my head at once!
Look, this has nothing to do with you.\nI mean, not SPECIFICALLY you, anyway.\nIt's just that...
Well, I have a responsibility\nto look after my sisters.
Wait, so WE'RE the reason you won't get\nhitched to Captain Richypants?!
Way to blow our hiding spot, idiot!
Oh, dear. Were you two eavesdropping?
Our underhanded sneakiness is SO\nnot the issue at the moment!
You can't get married because you think\nyou need to look after us—no, to look\nafter me?
I can't believe I was getting in the way\nof your happiness... I don't wanna be\nsome...some big fat BURDEN for you!
Renee, you mustn't just run off like that.\nYou had me really worried!
If you ever fall in love with somebody,\nRamona and me are gonna be fine!
So if you're into Mr. Moneybags,\ndon't let us hold you back!
I'm sorry, Renee. I didn't mean for what\nI said to come out like it did.
But I'm still not going to marry him.
I actually do dream of getting married.
Wait, really? ...Huh. I figured love\ndidn't hold much interest for ya.
Hee hee! Of course it does, Ramona!\nI think everyone dreams of love in\none form or another.
For me, what I want is to have a big,\nloving family like Mom and Dad did.

I have a plan for my romantic future,
Renee. I know what I'm doing—
and right now, that plan involves
staying right where I am.
Is that 'cause I'm holding you back?
It's because I want to see you SUCCEED.
You and Ramona both have oodles of\ntalent—and I want to support that in\nwhatever form it takes.
I just want the two of you to be happy.\nThat's my honest goal.
So ya ain't turnin' that guy down\nbecause of us?
No, Ramona. I'm just not ready to\nget married right now.
Mom and Dad wanted us to be happy\nabove all else, and that's a desire I share.
So what I want—what I TRULY want—\nis to stick around and help the two of\nyou find that happiness.
I'm not pretending to be Mom.\nI just have a plan—an order to things.

I wouldn't be truly happy if I pursued my
own desires while yours were unfulfilled.
Once you two are happy, I'll be happy—
in fact, I'll be TRIPLE happy!
Huh. I guess that makes sense.
In that case, I'm gonna hurry up and\nbecome the best blacksmith ever\nso we can all be happy!
Then you can find some other rich guy\nand I can come to your house and swim\naround in a huge pool of gold coins!
Glad ya have a plan all figured out, Sis.
I ain't sure what form my happiness is\ngonna take, but I know I'll find it someday.
So if ya wanna wait for that to happen,\nRena, I'll try to make it worthwhile.
There's no romance in the world that\ncould give me what the two of you do.
We've given our all to get here,\nand we ALL deserve true happiness!
